<paragraph blockId="18.[264,1323,284,875]" box="[312,1146,649,675]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Etymology. The specific epithet derives from the 
<typeStatus box="[892,942,649,675]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">type</typeStatus>
locality 
<collectingRegion box="[1044,1142,649,675]" country="China" name="Ningxia" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Ningxia</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[264,1323,284,875]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Comments. This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Yang" authorityName="Yang" box="[811,1195,689,715]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicicurvatus">
<emphasis box="[811,1127,689,714]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Chrysotimus apicicurvatus</emphasis>
Yang
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion country="China" name="Zhejiang" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Zhejiang</collectingRegion>
, but may be separated from the latter by the first flagellomere subtriangular, about as long as wide, surstylus and cercus slender. In 
<taxonomicName box="[825,1023,769,794]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicicurvatus">
<emphasis box="[825,1023,769,794]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">C. apicicurvatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the first flagellomere is 0.55 times as long as wide, surstylus and cercus are broad (Yang, 2001).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[264,1323,284,875]" box="[312,570,849,875]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Distribution. 
<collectingRegion box="[468,566,849,875]" country="China" name="Ningxia" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Ningxia</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
